    <refmeta>
      <refentrytitle>ss-download</refentrytitle>

      <manvolnum>1</manvolnum>
    </refmeta>

    <refnamediv>
      <refname>ss-download</refname>

      <refpurpose>attach an EBS volume to a running instance</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>

    <refsynopsisdiv>
      <cmdsynopsis>
        <command>ss-download</command>

        <arg><option>--targetdir</option></arg>

        <arg><option>--quiet</option></arg>

        <arg><option>--verbose</option></arg>

        <arg><option>-h</option> | <option>--help</option></arg>

        <arg choice="req" rep="norepeat"><replaceable>path</replaceable></arg>

        <arg><replaceable>output</replaceable></arg>

        <arg><replaceable>username</replaceable></arg>

        <arg><replaceable>password</replaceable></arg>
      </cmdsynopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>

    <refsection>
      <title>Description</title>

      <para>The <command>ss-download</command> command will download the
      artifact from the referenced path to the current working directory or to
      the specified target directory. If <replaceable>output</replaceable> is
      specified, it will be used for the local name; otherwise, the basename
      of the <replaceable>path</replaceable> is used. The
      <replaceable>username</replaceable> and
      <replaceable>password</replaceable> only need to be specified when
      running the command standalone outside of a SlipStream execution.</para>
    </refsection>

    <refsection>
      <title>Options</title>

      <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><option>--targetdir</option></term>

          <listitem>
            <para>The directory in which to write the downloaded artifact. By
            default, the current working directory is used.</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term><option>--quiet</option></term>

          <listitem>
            <para>Print minimal information.</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term><option>--verbose</option></term>

          <listitem>
            <para>Print additional information (default).</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term><option>-h</option>, <option>--help</option></term>

          <listitem>
            <para>Show this message.</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
    </refsection>
  </refentry>

